<subSubSection id="25AD655A13025C5CFF2DFEE8C968FD3A" pageId="6" pageNumber="459" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="6D0836D113025C5CFF2DFEE8C949FD9A" blockId="6.[166,1225,372,655]" pageId="6" pageNumber="459">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. This species was described three times — as 
<taxonomicName id="AAB74D5213025C5CFC50FEE8C992FE3B" authorityName="Meijere" authorityYear="1910" box="[934,1159,373,399]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Agromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="provecta">
<emphasis id="5FC3EAC313025C5CFC50FEE8C992FE3B" box="[934,1159,373,399]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="459">Agromyza provecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Indonesia, as 
<taxonomicName id="AAB74D5213025C5CFEB5FE08CF44FE1B" box="[323,593,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Agromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrisquama">
<emphasis id="5FC3EAC313025C5CFEB5FE08CF44FE1B" box="[323,593,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="459">Agromyza nigrisquama</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Formosa and as 
<taxonomicName id="AAB74D5213025C5CFCB9FE09C99CFE1B" authorityName="Spencer" authorityYear="1959" box="[847,1161,404,430]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="communis">
<emphasis id="5FC3EAC313025C5CFCB9FE09C99CFE1B" box="[847,1161,404,430]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="459">Melanagromyza communis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Belgian Congo and Mozambique and further was found in India and Ethiopia (
<bibRefCitation id="09264B2013025C5CFB94FE28CDF7FE5A" author="Spencer, K. A." pageId="6" pageNumber="459" pagination="233 - 254" refId="ref19874" refString="Spencer, K. A. 1977. Notes on world Agromyzidae, with the description of 16 new species. Beitrage zur Entomologie, 27 (2), 233 - 254." type="journal article" year="1977">Spencer, 1977</bibRefCitation>
), and Taiwan (
<bibRefCitation id="09264B2013025C5CFE7BFE49CF5DFE5A" author="Sasakawa, M." box="[397,584,468,495]" pageId="6" pageNumber="459" pagination="43 - 82" refId="ref19714" refString="Sasakawa, M. 1972. Formosan Agomyzidae (Diptera). Scientific Reports of the Kyoto Prefectural University, Agriculture, 24, 43 - 82." type="journal article" year="1972">Sasakawa, 1972</bibRefCitation>
). The nearest location to Ukraine where it was found in 2007 is Turkey (
<bibRefCitation id="09264B2013025C5CFEA9FE69CF96FDBA" author="Cikman, E. &amp; Sasakawa, M." box="[351,643,500,527]" pageId="6" pageNumber="459" pagination="71 - 78" refId="ref18877" refString="Cikman, E., Sasakawa, M. 2011. Contribution to the Agromyzidae (Diptera) fauna of Turkey. Turkish Journal of Zoology, 35 (1), 71 - 78. DOI: http: // doi. org / 10.3906 / zoo - 0908 - 12" type="journal article" year="2011">Çikman, Sasakawa, 2011</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="5FC3EAC313025C5CFD63FE68CE34FDBB" bold="true" box="[661,801,500,527]" pageId="6" pageNumber="459">
In 
<collectingCountry id="15A0764113025C5CFD40FE69CE09FDBB" box="[694,796,500,526]" name="Ukraine" pageId="6" pageNumber="459">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
.
</emphasis>
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313025C5CFCD1FE69CE9CFDBB" box="[807,905,500,526]" country="Ukraine" name="Kharkiv" pageId="6" pageNumber="459">Kharkiv</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313025C5CFC64FE69CEE2FDBB" box="[914,1015,500,526]" country="Ukraine" name="Luhans'k" pageId="6" pageNumber="459">Luhansk</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313025C5CFBD8FE69C970FDBB" box="[1070,1125,500,526]" country="Ukraine" name="Kyiv" pageId="6" pageNumber="459">Kyiv</collectingRegion>
Regions (
<bibRefCitation id="09264B2013025C5CFF58FD89CC58FD9A" author="Guglya, Yu." box="[174,333,532,559]" pageId="6" pageNumber="459" pagination="56 - 62" refId="ref19116" refString="Guglya, Yu. 2012. A study of the fauna of leaf-miner flies of the subfamily Agromyzinae (Diptera: Agromyzidae) of Ukraine. Report 2. 14 new species for the fauna of Ukraine. The first record of Melanagromyza provecta (de Meijere, 1910) for Europe. The Kharkov Entomological Society Gazette, 20 (2), 56 - 62 [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="2012">Guglya, 2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="09264B2013025C5CFEAEFD89CC86FD9A" author="Guglya, Yu." box="[344,403,532,559]" pageId="6" pageNumber="459" pagination="29 - 38" refId="ref19304" refString="Guglya, Yu. 2015. A study of the fauna of leaf-miner flies of the subfamily Agromyzinae (Diptera: Agromyzidae) of Ukraine. Report 3. Eleven new species for the fauna of Ukraine. The Kharkov Entomological Society Gazette, 23 (2), 29 - 38." type="journal article" year="2015">2015</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="09264B2013025C5CFE6BFD89CCFEFD9A" author="Guglya, Yu." box="[413,491,532,559]" pageId="6" pageNumber="459" pagination="17 - 24" refId="ref19357" refString="Guglya, Yu. 2016 a. A study of the fauna of leaf-miner flies of the subfamily Agromyzinae (Diptera: Agromyzidae) of Ukraine. Report 4. Thirteen new species for the fauna of Ukraine. The Kharkov Entomological Society Gazette, 24 (2), 17 - 24. URL: http: // nbuv. gov. ua / UJRN / Vkhet _ 2016 _ 24 _ 2 _ 7" type="journal article" year="2016">2016 a</bibRefCitation>
); 
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313025C5CFDF7FD89CFA6FD9B" box="[513,691,532,558]" country="Ukraine" name="Zakarpattya" pageId="6" pageNumber="459">Transcarpathia</collectingRegion>
and Vinnytsa Region (
<emphasis id="5FC3EAC313025C5CFC34FD89C95FFD9A" bold="true" box="[962,1098,532,559]" pageId="6" pageNumber="459">first record</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D0836D113025C5CFF2DFDA9C968FD3A" blockId="6.[166,1225,372,655]" pageId="6" pageNumber="459">
Bionomics. Collected material from 
<collectingCountry id="15A0764113025C5CFD5FFDA9CE1CFDFB" box="[681,777,564,590]" name="Ukraine" pageId="6" pageNumber="459">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
dates from 17 May to 19 September, so two or three generations develops per year. 
<taxonomicName id="AAB74D5213025C5CFD3BFDC8CE42FDDB" authorityName="Meijere" authorityYear="1910" box="[717,855,597,622]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Agromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="provecta">
<emphasis id="5FC3EAC313025C5CFD3BFDC8CE42FDDB" box="[717,855,597,622]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="459">M. provecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="15A0764113025C5CFC88FDC9CECBFDDB" box="[894,990,596,622]" name="Ukraine" pageId="6" pageNumber="459">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
is common but not numerous. The only host plant has been known for this species is 
<taxonomicName id="AAB74D5213025C5CFC51FDE9C960FD3B" box="[935,1141,628,654]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Abutilon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="6" pageNumber="459" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="indicum">
<emphasis id="5FC3EAC313025C5CFC51FDE9C960FD3B" box="[935,1141,628,654]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="459">Abutilon indicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
